266
00:12:46,171 --> 00:12:46,601
Umm...

267
00:12:46,601 --> 00:12:47,201
Umm...
Hello, this is Koizumi.

268
00:12:47,201 --> 00:12:48,031
Hello, this is Koizumi.

269
00:12:48,731 --> 00:12:51,241
Why are you
with Miss Asahina?!

270
00:12:51,241 --> 00:12:53,311
Certain circumstances
came up.

271
00:12:53,311 --> 00:12:55,441
Would it be possible for you
to come join us right now?

272
00:12:55,441 --> 00:12:57,471
Of course!
I'll be right there!

273
00:13:17,131 --> 00:13:19,761
What in the world happened,
Miss Asahina?

274
00:13:20,331 --> 00:13:25,101
Kyon... I can't return
to the future!

275
00:13:28,911 --> 00:13:30,341
Can't return?

276
00:13:30,341 --> 00:13:32,681
Err... What do you mean,
can't return?

277
00:13:32,681 --> 00:13:34,271
In other words,
this is what's going on.

278
00:13:35,511 --> 00:13:39,141
We are going through an eternal loop
of the same time period.

279
00:13:40,321 --> 00:13:41,191
What?

280
00:13:41,191 --> 00:13:44,591
We are going through an eternal loop
of the same time period.

281
00:13:45,521 --> 00:13:47,861
We are going through
an eternal loop...

282
00:13:47,861 --> 00:13:51,331
Koizumi, do you realize
what you're saying?

283
00:13:51,331 --> 00:13:55,301
I do. Much more than
I wish I did.

284
00:13:55,301 --> 00:13:57,801
I had just been speaking
with Miss Asahina.

285
00:13:57,801 --> 00:13:58,771
Call me too.

286
00:13:58,771 --> 00:14:00,671
And as a result, what we realized
was that recently,

287
00:14:00,671 --> 00:14:03,941
the flow of time
was a bit strange.

288
00:14:03,941 --> 00:14:07,111
You might want to credit this
to Miss Asahina.

289
00:14:07,111 --> 00:14:09,851
Thanks to her, I was
able to confirm it.

290
00:14:09,851 --> 00:14:10,951
Confirm what?

291
00:14:10,951 --> 00:14:17,991
That we have experienced the same
span of time numerous times.

292
00:14:17,991 --> 00:14:19,631
You said that earlier.

293
00:14:19,631 --> 00:14:22,291
To be precise, we've been
repeating the time

294
00:14:22,291 --> 00:14:24,231
from August 17th
to the 31 st.

295
00:14:24,561 --> 00:14:28,831
We're in the middle of an
endless summer vacation.

296
00:14:28,831 --> 00:14:31,601
Well, we're certainly
in the middle.

297
00:14:31,601 --> 00:14:34,811
It's a never-ending
endless summer.

298
00:14:34,811 --> 00:14:40,481
This world has lost all time
after September 1 st.

299
00:14:40,481 --> 00:14:44,011
That is why Miss Asahina
cannot return to the future.

300
00:14:44,381 --> 00:14:46,521
I suppose you could say
that it's natural

301
00:14:46,521 --> 00:14:48,421
that she can't return to a
future that doesn't exist.

302
00:14:48,421 --> 00:14:52,831
Cut it out. What's natural about
something as stupid as that?

303
00:14:52,831 --> 00:14:54,821
Who'd believe it?

304
00:14:56,501 --> 00:14:59,231
We'd like for you
to believe it.

305
00:15:00,671 --> 00:15:04,871
Umm... I'll explain, too.

306
00:15:04,871 --> 00:15:10,011
Well... because of
"classified information",

307
00:15:10,011 --> 00:15:15,281
I'm always contacting the future
and "classified information"-ing,

308
00:15:16,881 --> 00:15:19,951
but I hadn't received
any "classified information"

309
00:15:19,951 --> 00:15:22,721
for about a week or so,
and I thought, "that's strange."

310
00:15:22,721 --> 00:15:25,861
And so I
"classified information"...

311
00:15:25,861 --> 00:15:29,531
I was so surprised, I tried to "classified",

312
00:15:29,531 --> 00:15:31,031
I was so surprised, I tried to "classified",
Miss Asahina, are your "classified"s

313
00:15:31,031 --> 00:15:33,471
but it was completely "classified"...
Miss Asahina, are your "classified"s

314
00:15:33,471 --> 00:15:34,331
but it was completely "classified"...
things that can't be said on TV?

315
00:15:34,331 --> 00:15:35,861
Things that can't be said on TV?

316
00:15:39,201 --> 00:15:45,011
Are we trapped inside one of
those closed spaces?

317
00:15:45,011 --> 00:15:46,811
That's not it.

318
00:15:46,811 --> 00:15:49,711
A single portion of time
has been torn away.

319
00:15:50,421 --> 00:15:54,221
At exactly the point when it becomes
midnight on August 31 st,

320
00:15:54,221 --> 00:15:58,961
everything resets, and we go back to
August 17th. That's the process.

321
00:15:58,961 --> 00:16:02,191
So what about our...
No, humanity's memories?

322
00:16:02,191 --> 00:16:07,101
Those are reset as well. Everything
starts over from the beginning.

323
00:16:07,571 --> 00:16:10,131
So you mean that time does that
thing that you mentioned.

324
00:16:12,401 --> 00:16:14,571
Well, I guess it
can't be helped.

325
00:16:14,571 --> 00:16:17,601
Oh no, Miss Asahina
isn't involved in this.

326
00:16:18,241 --> 00:16:19,981
Okay, then, what is?

327
00:16:19,981 --> 00:16:21,611
I would guess
Miss Suzumiya.

328
00:16:25,021 --> 00:16:28,351
I'm sure she doesn't realize it,
but somewhere inside of her

329
00:16:28,351 --> 00:16:31,491
is a desire to not let
summer vacation end.

330
00:16:31,491 --> 00:16:34,561
Do you mean she feels
regret over something?

331
00:16:34,561 --> 00:16:36,261
That's what I believe.

332
00:16:36,261 --> 00:16:39,531
Perhaps she feels that
there's something left

333
00:16:39,531 --> 00:16:41,501
that she wants to do during
our summer vacation?

334
00:16:42,271 --> 00:16:46,671
Man, the hopeless situations she causes
unfold on a galactic scale.

335
00:16:49,981 --> 00:16:51,981
I've been wondering this
since I got here,

336
00:16:51,981 --> 00:16:54,181
but you seem awfully
cheerful about this.

337
00:16:54,181 --> 00:16:56,081
It's because we've finally
been able to solve

338
00:16:56,081 --> 00:16:59,321
the recent mysterious and frequent
feelings of deja vu that I've had.

339
00:16:59,321 --> 00:17:01,791
Now that I think about it, those inexplicable
feelings may have been

340
00:17:01,791 --> 00:17:04,551
remnants from when our memories
have been reset.

341
00:17:06,391 --> 00:17:08,761
You've been feeling
them too, right?

342
00:17:10,731 --> 00:17:13,561
Is it possible that other people
across the world feel this, too?

343
00:17:15,501 --> 00:17:18,341
You and I
are a special case.

344
00:17:18,341 --> 00:17:20,811
It appears that the people who
are closest to Miss Suzumiya

345
00:17:20,811 --> 00:17:23,611
are able to sense
this strangeness.

346
00:17:23,611 --> 00:17:26,881
What about Haruhi? Does she
sense any of this at all?

347
00:17:26,881 --> 00:17:32,751
Not at all, it seems. It would probably
be bad for us if she did.

348
00:17:33,791 --> 00:17:39,931
However, I believe that there is one
person who remembers everything,

349
00:17:39,931 --> 00:17:43,261
more than the deja vu
that we do.

350
00:17:44,301 --> 00:17:46,771
And who would
that be?

351
00:17:46,771 --> 00:17:48,201
I think you know.

352
00:17:51,641 --> 00:17:53,641
Is that right, Nagato?

353
00:17:53,641 --> 00:17:54,771
It is.

354
00:17:54,771 --> 00:17:56,611
You remember
all of it?

355
00:17:56,611 --> 00:17:57,841
Yes.

356
00:17:59,381 --> 00:18:03,321
So, how many times have we repeated
all of this, this time?

357
00:18:03,321 --> 00:18:07,271
This is the fifteen thousandth,
four hundred and ninety-ninth time.

358
00:18:08,821 --> 00:18:11,921
15,499?

359
00:18:11,921 --> 00:18:17,091
What do you mean by 15,499?
Nagato, what are you saying?

360
00:18:18,561 --> 00:18:21,431
Are you serious?

361
00:18:21,431 --> 00:18:22,371
I am.

362
00:18:22,371 --> 00:18:27,341
You're saying that we've done the
exact same things that many times?

363
00:18:27,341 --> 00:18:29,341
They're not all guaranteed
to happen.

364
00:18:29,341 --> 00:18:34,181
Out of 15,499 repetitions,
there are two occasions,

365
00:18:34,181 --> 00:18:38,281
#2,391 and #11,054, where we
did not go to a Bon festival.

366
00:18:38,281 --> 00:18:40,591
A pattern where we did
go to a Bon festival,

367
00:18:40,591 --> 00:18:43,861
but did not go to a goldfish
scooping stand, occurred 437 times.

368
00:18:43,861 --> 00:18:46,791
We've had a part-time job 9,026 times,
and when we did,

369
00:18:46,791 --> 00:18:49,091
there are six different kinds
of jobs that we did.

370
00:18:49,091 --> 00:18:50,761
In addition to handing
out balloons,

371
00:18:50,761 --> 00:18:53,531
we also worked as movers, cashiers,
we handed out fliers,

372
00:18:53,531 --> 00:18:54,301
worked as call center...

373
00:18:54,301 --> 00:18:54,771
worked as call center...
I got it, that's enough.

374
00:18:54,771 --> 00:18:56,101
I got it, that's enough.

375
00:19:04,181 --> 00:19:09,481
15,499 times,
that's what Nagato said.

376
00:19:10,051 --> 00:19:14,711
Times two weeks, hmm,
that's around 594 years.

377
00:19:15,251 --> 00:19:19,421
She alone has memories
of all that time,

378
00:19:19,421 --> 00:19:21,961
repeating it all
over and over...

379
00:19:21,961 --> 00:19:23,731
Nagato, how must it feel

380
00:19:23,731 --> 00:19:27,601
to experience that same period
of time over and over again?

381
00:19:30,541 --> 00:19:33,001
I've heard yet another
crazy story.

382
00:19:34,611 --> 00:19:37,841
The next day we
went stargazing.

383
00:19:37,841 --> 00:19:40,011
The location was
Nagato's apartment,

384
00:19:40,011 --> 00:19:42,881
and the telescope was one that
Koizumi had gotten for us.

385
00:19:45,381 --> 00:19:49,551
I'm bored of this.
UFOs. Let's look for UFOs.

386
00:19:49,551 --> 00:19:54,391
Hey! Stop it, Haruhi,
you'll break it!

387
00:19:59,431 --> 00:20:02,561
Exactly what does
she want to do?

388
00:20:03,001 --> 00:20:05,231
Now what could
that be?

389
00:20:05,671 --> 00:20:08,501
If we could figure that out,
this would all be solved...

390
00:20:09,881 --> 00:20:12,181
How about trying
this out?

391
00:20:12,181 --> 00:20:14,981
Give Miss Suzumiya a sudden
embrace from behind,

392
00:20:14,981 --> 00:20:18,081
then whisper "I love you"
into her ear.

393
00:20:18,081 --> 00:20:19,851
And who would
be doing that?

394
00:20:19,851 --> 00:20:22,321
Is there anyone else who could
fill the role other than you?

395
00:20:22,321 --> 00:20:24,021
Consider me out.

396
00:20:25,091 --> 00:20:27,351
All right, how about
if I do it?

397
00:20:31,861 --> 00:20:36,101
I'm kidding. I'm lacking a certain
something for the role.

398
00:20:36,101 --> 00:20:37,441
And all that would
do is cause

399
00:20:37,441 --> 00:20:39,271
unnecessary confusion
in Miss Suzumiya.

400
00:20:41,811 --> 00:20:45,801
We continued to run through a torrent
of summer vacation events.

401
00:20:46,851 --> 00:20:49,051
We went to a batting center,

402
00:20:49,051 --> 00:20:51,481
to a real fireworks show,

403
00:20:51,481 --> 00:20:53,721
and we even took part in a
goby fishing tournament.

404
00:20:53,721 --> 00:20:55,721
We also had a test
of courage,

405
00:20:55,721 --> 00:20:56,991
watched some movies,

406
00:20:56,991 --> 00:20:59,261
went to the beach,
went bowling,

407
00:20:59,261 --> 00:21:03,251
and even to karaoke.
We were always doing something.

408
00:21:03,801 --> 00:21:08,101
Of course, I knew that this wasn't
going to satisfy Haruhi.

409
00:21:08,101 --> 00:21:11,041
Even still, there wasn't anything
I could do about it,

410
00:21:11,041 --> 00:21:15,101
and the last days of our summer
vacation ticked away.

411
00:21:15,571 --> 00:21:19,911
And so we ended up
at August 30th...

412
00:21:22,151 --> 00:21:25,311
With this, we've finished
everything on our list.

413
00:21:30,691 --> 00:21:33,091
Hmm. I wonder if this
was good enough.

414
00:21:33,691 --> 00:21:36,721
But, hmm, well...
I guess this works.

415
00:21:37,261 --> 00:21:40,101
Hey, is there anything else
you want to do?

416
00:21:43,971 --> 00:21:45,371
That's fine, then.

417
00:21:45,371 --> 00:21:47,841
We were able to do
a lot this summer,

418
00:21:47,841 --> 00:21:49,341
so that's enough, right?

419
00:21:49,341 --> 00:21:54,541
No, Haruhi...
You're still not satisfied.

420
00:21:55,711 --> 00:21:57,821
Okay, we're done
for today.

421
00:21:57,821 --> 00:21:59,681
I had tomorrow set aside
just in case,

422
00:21:59,681 --> 00:22:01,991
but you can just
take the day off.

423
00:22:01,991 --> 00:22:04,251
Let's meet again in the clubroom
the day after tomorrow.

424
00:22:07,761 --> 00:22:09,061
Wait, Haruhi.

425
00:22:10,601 --> 00:22:12,291
There it is again!
That deja vu!

426
00:22:12,861 --> 00:22:15,461
And it's a strong one,
stronger than ever before.

427
00:22:16,231 --> 00:22:19,641
I can't let Haruhi leave.
If she goes,

428
00:22:19,641 --> 00:22:21,711
we'll end up repeating
these past two weeks

429
00:22:21,711 --> 00:22:24,441
for the some-thousandth
time again.

430
00:22:24,841 --> 00:22:27,351
But what should I do?

431
00:22:27,351 --> 00:22:29,281
What should I say?

432
00:22:29,281 --> 00:22:32,781
There must have been a hint
somewhere in what Haruhi said.

433
00:22:32,781 --> 00:22:34,051
But what was it?

434
00:22:34,851 --> 00:22:37,451
What has she said
up to this point?

435
00:22:39,361 --> 00:22:40,351
I don't know...

436
00:22:42,161 --> 00:22:43,531
I can't remember...

437
00:22:59,411 --> 00:23:03,751
August 31 st. I haven't
touched my homework.

438
00:23:05,751 --> 00:23:08,781
Whatever, it doesn't
matter anymore.

439
00:23:11,721 --> 00:23:14,261
If we're just going to
do it all over again,

440
00:23:14,261 --> 00:23:17,461
then there's no point
to doing it.

441
00:23:25,271 --> 00:23:27,811
Whether tomorrow
comes or not,

442
00:23:27,811 --> 00:23:31,771
I'll leave it to the me at
that time to deal with it.

443
00:23:43,591 --> 00:23:46,161
Sora kara ochite kitanda
It fell from the sky

444
00:23:46,161 --> 00:23:48,861
Subete no negai wo nosete
With all of the wishes
that were made upon it

445
00:23:48,861 --> 00:23:53,421
Hitotsu no hoshi niwa
chotto omokatta kana
Maybe it was a little too heavy
for a single star

446
00:23:54,101 --> 00:23:56,701
Yappari nanika henda yo
Something just doesn't
seem right

447
00:23:56,701 --> 00:23:59,371
Kokoro no kimi ga kieta
The image of you in my mind
has vanished

448
00:23:59,371 --> 00:24:03,581
Tashika ni oboeteru tte
ieruno kai?
Can I say that I
remember you clearly?

449
00:24:03,581 --> 00:24:05,081
Tomare!
Stop!

450
00:24:05,081 --> 00:24:08,881
Kako wa jibun no mono
The past belongs to me

451
00:24:08,881 --> 00:24:13,451
Touzen daretomo torikaetakunai
Of course I don't want to trade it
with anyone else

452
00:24:13,451 --> 00:24:14,821
Nazenara
That's because

453
00:24:14,821 --> 00:24:20,031
Basudei datta watashitachi niwa
It was my birthday,
and when we saw each other

454
00:24:20,031 --> 00:24:22,831
Deai ga umareta toki ni
We could see the first dream

455
00:24:22,831 --> 00:24:25,231
Hajimete no yume ga mieru
That we had
when we were born

456
00:24:25,231 --> 00:24:30,141
Doushiyouka tte
nayanda koto mo
Worrying about
"what do I do?"

457
00:24:30,141 --> 00:24:34,041
Ima omoeba waraeru hodo
datta yo ne
Is laughable when I
think about it now

458
00:24:34,041 --> 00:24:36,741
Mou wasureteta
I've already forgotten it

459
00:24:36,741 --> 00:24:38,801
Kimi wo sagasou
Let's search for you

